Downvote removed. It works for quite a few people here (as evidenced by this being in the positives), but I can't say it works for me. To be more specific, when I tend to think of this kind of format, SCP-092 comes to mind. There's obviously ways to differentiate (and I think this differentiates enough from that), but it doesn't feel too unique or compelling to me. The ones I did get interested in were SCP-2263-18 and SCP-2263-27, and the reasons why I think that is (beyond their effects) is because they feel a bit more personal to the creator of them, and seem more genuine.

Also, SCP-2263-60, because I'm a sucker for music stuff.







